## Part 6 — The code (each file = one job)

```
   IDEA (from the story)            ->   FILE (in the repo)

   the whole library + librarian    ->   ragshield_core/retriever.py
   the three AIs (Lias)             ->   ragshield_core/llm_backends.py
   Ring 1 (Door Guard)              ->   ragshield_core/ring1_ingest.py
   Ring 2 (Sorter)                  ->   ragshield_core/ring2_retrieval.py
   Ring 3 (Three Judges)            ->   ragshield_core/ring3_consensus.py
   the BOSS that runs all of it     ->   ragshield_core/rag_shield.py
   the buttons & screen you click   ->   frontend/app.py + pages/
   the scorecard (how good are we)  ->   evaluation/run_experiments.py
```

- **retriever.py** — the library + librarian. Stores documents, fetches top matches,
  can inject/remove fake books. Demo = TF-IDF; real = FAISS 5000-doc index.
- **llm_backends.py** — one switch to talk to any AI (Claude / LLaMA / Azure / mock).
  Builds the 3-AI panel for Ring 3.
- **ring1_ingest.py** — Door Guard: perplexity + pattern + outlier checks; blocks fakes.
- **ring2_retrieval.py** — Sorter: provenance + consistency; re-ranks, drops low-trust.
- **ring3_consensus.py** — Three Judges: AIs vote; disagreement -> drop suspect, re-ask.
- **rag_shield.py** — the Boss. defense=False -> attack wins (proves problem);
  defense=True -> rings on (proves fix). Produces a full trace.
- **frontend/** — 5 pages: Attack, Defense, Side-by-Side, Forensic, Dashboard.
- **evaluation/run_experiments.py** — the scorecard; prints 90% -> 13%.

