## Part 8 — Teach it in 60 seconds (memorize)

"An AI answers questions by first grabbing a few documents from a library and reading
them. The attack sneaks 5 fake documents into that library so the AI reads lies and
gives the wrong answer — and it works 90% of the time. The easy fixes are single gates,
so attackers just walk through them. Our fix, RAG-Shield, uses three gates at three
moments: a door guard that blocks fake documents on entry, a sorter that distrusts
documents that disagree with the others, and three AI judges that must agree or we
re-check. To win, a fake now has to beat all three at once — and that drops the attack
from 90% to 13%. In the code, each gate is its own file, a boss file runs them in order,
and a flag turns the defense on or off so we can show before and after."

