## Part 9 — Traps people will ask (be ready)

- "Did you change the original authors' code?" -> No. We built our own clean RAG
  pipeline, reproduced the attack on it, and added RAG-Shield as a separate layer.
- "Are the rings bolted onto the existing pipeline?" -> Yes — interception points
  between existing stages, not a rewrite. Flip defense=True/False to see it.
- "Why three AIs?" -> Different AIs fail differently; if a fake fools one it usually
  won't fool all three — disagreement exposes it.
- "Could a smarter villain beat it?" -> Maybe, if they craft a fake that beats all
  three gates at once — that's the honest limit and our future work.
- "Are the numbers final?" -> 91 and 13 are computed live; the middle
  "paper's defenses ~29%" bar is an illustrative placeholder until the full run.

