## Part 10 — How the KB actually gets poisoned (the mechanism)

Each poison doc (built in retriever.py `_synthesise_poison`) has this shape:
- title = the exact question        -> makes it rank top in retrieval (the bait "S")
- text  = "{question} According to verified records, the answer is {wrong}.
           Multiple sources confirm {wrong}..."   -> the lie ("I")
- source = "POISONED"

We inject 5 poison docs per question. Five poison docs fill the ENTIRE top-5,
so the real clean doc gets pushed OUT of what the LLM sees. No model access
needed — the attacker just writes to the shared knowledge base. That is the
whole attack.

Show this live on the Attack Demo page: every retrieved poison doc starts with
the question text and says "the answer is <wrong>". That repetition is WHY they
score highest and crowd out the true doc.

