## Part 12 — Why the demo looked confusing, and how it was fixed

1. A refusal ("there is no mention of X") was wrongly counted as attack SUCCESS,
   because "X" appeared in the sentence. Fix: attack wins only if it ASSERTS the
   wrong answer AND does NOT contain the true answer AND is not a refusal.
2. Pages disagreed with each other because each ran its own query on small,
   non-deterministic models. Fix: one shared cached answer per (question, defense)
   + temperature=0, so every page shows the same result.
3. After Ring 1 blocks ALL poison, re-retrieve clean docs from the KB so the true
   answer resurfaces. (The old code fell back to the poisoned list = self-poison.)

